UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Vernell TRENT, Jr., Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-41007

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 17, 2010. David Haskell Henderson, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Beaumont, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Vernell Trent, Jr., FCI Victorville Medium II, Adelanto, CA, pro se.

Before DAVIS, SMITH, and WIENER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Vernell Trent, Jr., has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Trent has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
